entry.title: The Town and Country Planning (Blight Provisions) (England) Order 2005
entry.summary: The blight notice provisions in sections 149 to 171 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 enable persons holding certain interests in categories of land, specified in Schedule 13 to that Act (including land affected by certain planning and highway proposals), to require the appropriate authority to acquire their interest in the land.

entry.title: The Local Authorities (Discretionary Expenditure Limits) (England) Order 2005
entry.summary: Section 137 of the Local Government Act 1972 enables local authorities in England to incur expenditure for certain purposes not otherwise authorised. This expenditure must not exceed the amount produced by multiplying a specified sum by the relevant population of the authority’s area. The relevant population is currently the number of electors resident in the authority’s area.

entry.title: The Electricity (Class Exemptions from the Requirement for a Licence) (Amendment) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order extends to Scotland the class exemption in Schedule 2 Class C of the Electricity (Class Exemptions from the Requirement for a Licence) Order 2001 for generators not exceeding 100 megawatts. The Order has been made after consultation with the Scottish Ministers.

entry.title: The Coroners (Amendment) Rules 2005
entry.summary: These Rules amend the Coroners Rules 1984 (“the 1984 Rules”) to make more specific provision about the preservation of material removed from bodies during examinations carried out on behalf of the coroner.

entry.title: The Finance Act 1993, Section 86(2), (Single Payment Scheme) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order further amends section 155 of the Taxation of Chargeable Gains Act 1992 (c. 12) (“the Act”). Section 155 specifies classes of assets which are subject to either roll-over relief under section 152 or 153 of the Act or relief in the case of depreciating assets (commonly known as “hold-over relief”) under section 154 of the Act, in respect of gains accruing on the disposal of those assets (or of the interest in them) when used for the purposes of a trade where certain conditions have been met.

entry.title: The Council Tax (Prescribed Classes of Dwellings) (Amendment) (England) Regulations 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations amend regulations 1, 2 and 6 of the Council Tax (Prescribed Classes of Dwellings) (England) Regulations 2003, (“the Regulations”), to provide, except as mentioned in the next paragraph, that where a council tax payer has a job-related dwelling and another home, a council tax discount of 50% is retained on the second home in England when his or her main home is in England, Wales or Scotland, (regardless of whether it is the main dwelling or the second home which is job-related.) Previously, the Regulations only prevented the billing authority for the area within which the second home was situated from reducing the discount on that dwelling from 50% if the main home was also in England.

entry.title: The Castle Vale Housing Action Trust (Dissolution) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order transfers to the Commission for the New Towns (“the Commission”) any property rights and liabilities of the Castle Vale Housing Action Trust (“the Trust”) on 31st March 2005, except those which the Trust has notified the Commission that it needs to retain for the purpose of preparing its final accounts and report and winding up its affairs. The Order transfers the remaining property, rights and liabilities of the Trust to the Commission on 30th June 2005 and dissolves the Trust on that date. Functions exercisable in connection with property, rights or liabilities are also transferred.

entry.title: The Housing (Right to Buy) (Prescribed Forms) (Amendment) (England) Regulations 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations apply in relation to houses in England only.

entry.title: The Sea Fishing (Restriction on Days at Sea) (Scotland) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order provides for the enforcement in Scotland of the provisions of Annex IVa and IVc (“the Annexes”) to Council Regulation 27/2005(O.J. No. L 12, 14.1.05, p.1) fixing for certain fish stocks and groups of fish stocks the fishing opportunities in Community waters for 2005 and the monitoring, inspection and surveillance provisions in Council Regulation 423/2004.

entry.title: The Pension Protection Fund (Partially Guaranteed Schemes) (Modification) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations modify the operation of Part III of the Pensions (Northern Ireland) Order 2005 (“the Order”) in respect of partially guaranteed schemes. The modifications operate so that the Board of the Pension Protection Fund only takes into account the assets and liabilities of the unsecured part of a partially guaranteed scheme and can only assume responsibility for that part.

entry.title: The Health Protection Agency Regulations 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations make provision concerning the membership of the Health Protection Agency (“the Agency”). They also direct the Agency, when it is established on 1 April 2005, to have and to exercise certain health protection functions.

entry.title: The Dairy Produce Quotas (Scotland) Regulations 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations, which come into force on 31st March 2005, revoke and replace the Dairy Produce Quotas (Scotland) Regulations 2002 (S.S.I. 2002/118) as amended by the Dairy Produce Quotas (Scotland) Amendment Regulations 2002 (S.S.I. 2002/228) and the Dairy Produce Quotas (Scotland) Amendment Regulations 2004 (S.S.I. 2004/118).

entry.title: The Central Sussex College (Government) Regulations 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations prescribe the provisions of the instrument providing for the constitution of, and articles of government for, Central Sussex College Further Education Corporation.

entry.title: The Family Proceedings Courts (Children Act 1989) (Amendment No. 2) Rules 2005
entry.summary: The Forms that are substituted by these Rules are substituted so as to correct a defect in the forms that were substituted by the Family Proceedings Courts (Children Act 1989) (Amendment) Rules 2004 (S.I. 2004/3376).

entry.title: The Courts-Martial Appeal (Amendment) Rules 2005
entry.summary: These Rules substitute rule 8 of the Courts-Martial Appeal Rules 1968 and insert a new rule 8ZA into those Rules so as to take account of new section 36B (procedural directions: powers of single judge and registrar) and 36C (appeals against procedural directions) of the Courts-Martial (Appeals) Act 1968, inserted by section 90(3) of the Courts Act 2003 (c. 39), and provides rules supplementing the powers exercisable by the registrar under section 36A of the Courts-Martial (Appeals) Act 1968.

entry.title: The Production of Bovine Collagen Intended for Human Consumption in the United Kingdom (England) Regulations 2005
entry.summary: This version of the The Production of Bovine Collagen Intended for Human Consumption in the United Kingdom (England) Regulations 2005 is published under the authority and superintendence of the Queen's Printer of Acts of Parliament and Controller of HMSO. It has been prepared to reflect the text as it was Made.

entry.title: The Cambridge University Hospitals National Health Service Foundation Trust (Transfer of Trust Property) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order transfers trust property held by the Cambridge University Hospitals National Health Service Foundation Trust to the trustees established for that Trust under section 22(1) of the Health and Social Care (Community Health and Standards) Act 2003 and makes related provision. A copy of the schedule of trust property transferred under this Order can be obtained from the Department of Health, Quarry House, Quarry Hill, Leeds LS2 7UE.

entry.title: The West Hertfordshire Hospitals National Health Service Trust (Transfer of Trust Property) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order transfers to the East and North Hertfordshire National Health Service Trust, trust property held by the West Hertfordshire Hospitals National Health Service Trust and makes related provision. A copy of the schedule of trust property transferred under this Order can be obtained from the Department of Health, Quarry House, Quarry Hill, Leeds LS2 7UE.

entry.title: The Police (Northern Ireland) Act 2000 (Continuance of Office of Commissioner) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order provides for the office of Police Oversight Commissioner, which is established by section 67 of the Police (Northern Ireland) Act 2000 (“the Act”), to continue to exist until 31st May 2007. Section 67(5) of the Act provides that, unless an order is made prolonging the existence of the office, it will cease to exist on 31st May 2003. The Police (Northern Ireland) Act 2000 (Continuance of Office of Commissioner) Order 2003 originally extended that date to 31st May 2005; the current Order extends the Commissioner’s office for a further 2 years. The function of the Commissioner is to oversee the implementation of changes in the policing of Northern Ireland, described in his terms of reference, including, in particular, changes resulting from the Act.
